OL,3,CVictim: 'While others were building
OL,4,Ctheir futures, I was reliving my
OL,5,Ctrauma'
OL,7,FShe added: "I missed out on valuable
OL,8,Fworkshops and placements at law firms
OL,9,Fbecause they clashed with court dates."
OL,11,FShe explained how his offending had
OL,12,Fmade it "incredibly difficult" to form
OL,13,Frelationships and how she was having
OL,14,Fweekly therapy to cope with the
OL,15,Fpsychological damage he had caused.
OL,17,FDS Kate Hughes, of Operation
OL,18,FBluestone, the specialist rape and
OL,19,Fsexual offences team, praised the
OL,20,Fvictim's bravery in coming forward to
OL,21,Freport the incident.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
